Privacy Policy
Effective date:
January 20, 2024
Welcome! This Privacy Policy explains
how
and why Axlebolt Ltd. (“Axlebolt“, “we” or derivatives) processes your personal
data (the “Policy”) while you play the
Standoff
2
mobile
game (the “Game").
We can change the Policy. If we make
significant changes to it, we will send you an in-Game notification before the
changes take effect. The changes will take effect 15 days after publication. If
you use the Game from the effective date of the changes, you agree to the new
version of the Policy.
In addition to the Policy, please also
review the
Terms of Use and the Rules of the Game
.
Who are we?
We are Axlebolt Limited
(Axlebolt LTD).
We are:
• the controller of
your personal data, that is, we independently determine how and why we process
your personal data (the “
Controller
");
• the processor of your
personal data, that is, we process your personal data (hereinafter referred to
as the “
Processor
").
Axlebolt is established
and operates in accordance with the laws of the Republic of Cyprus. Registration
No.: HE 409660. Registered address: Christodoulou Chatzipavlou, 221, Helios
Court, Flat 401, 3036, Limassol, Cyprus.
Since access to the
Game is provided remotely, we may inadvertently collect personal data from
persons under the age of 16. If you are a minor, please make sure that your
parent or legal representative has read and understood the provisions of the
Policy. The Policy on behalf of the minor is accepted and confirmed by the
legal representative of the minor. If you are a minor and cannot familiarize
your legal representative with the provisions of this Policy, as well as if you
(your legal representative) do not agree with the terms of this Policy,
immediately stop further use of the Game.
If a legal
representative allows a minor to use the Game, then such legal representative
has read and understood the Policy, as well as accepted the Policy on behalf of
the minor.
What principles do we
follow when processing your personal data?
•
Lawfulness
. We
process personal data only legally (with your consent, by virtue of the law,
based on legitimate interest, on other legitimate grounds) and for specific
purposes, as well as for the proper provision of services to provide access to
the Game.
•
Transparency.
We strive to be as clear and open as possible about how we collect, use and
share personal data. If you have any questions about any provisions of the
Policy, we are open to communication.
•
Fairness
. We
do not allow the processing of personal data in an unreasonably harmful,
discriminatory, unexpected or misleading way.
•
Specified,
explicit and legitimate purposes.
The purposes of processing your personal
data can be found in the “Processing purposes” section of the Policy. We do not
process personal data for purposes not specified in this section.
•
Data minimization
.
We process data only to the extent necessary to achieve the processing
objectives.
•
Accuracy
. We
keep your personal data up-to-date.
•
Storage limitation
.
We do not store personal data for longer than is necessary for processing
purposes.
•
Integrity and
confidentiality
. We strive to ensure the security of your data by
protecting it from unauthorized or illegal processing, as well as from
accidental loss, destruction or damage, using appropriate technical and
organizational measures.
What personal data does
Axlebolt collect?
When you play Game and
share your personal data with Axlebolt, we act as a Processor and Controller of
your personal data.
We strive to collect as
little personal data as possible from users of our Game. Most of the data we
collect about you does not allow us to uniquely identify you as an individual,
however, in some cases it allows us to identify your device that you use to
access our Game (the “Device”).
We collect the
following data, which may be considered personal data in some countries:
The data that you
provide
We collect the data
that you provide yourself when using the Game. You have the right not to
provide this data, but certain functions will not be available to you.
These data include:
• “
User's email
"
- your unique email address.
• “
Username
"
is a set of characters and/or numbers that are not yet used by another player
in our Game, and which you can change in your account yourself. You can specify
the Username yourself, but this is optional. If you refuse to specify a
Username, it will be assigned randomly in an automatic manner.
• “
User’s Avatar
"
is an image or photo that you can, but are not required to upload to your
account instead of the default avatar.
• “
Information
provided when contacting support
” - information provided by you when
contacting our support service, including the nature of your problem, payments
data and information about your account.
• “
Information that
you share in text chats
” - information that is provided by you during
communication with other players through the messaging functionality in the
Game.
The data that we
collect automatically
• “
Location
Information
" – general information about your location (without
information about the exact geolocation) at the time when you are playing Game
(for example, IP address, country and city).
• “
Device
Information
" – technical data about your Device. For example, the
device ID; the serial number of the device; the name of your Internet service
Provider (ISP); the name of your browser and the plug-ins used; the operating
system and its version; information about hacking the device (“jailbreak”);
information about the network; the brand and manufacturer of your device; the
language you selected for the device; the version of the Game installed on your
device; the installation path of the Game; downloaded software libraries; your
carrier.
• “
Login information
”
- information about the time, location and IP when you log in to the Game.
• “
User’s ID
"
is a unique number (code) automatically generated and assigned to your account
to identify it in the Game.
• “
Information about
behavioral actions in the Game
” - information about your gaming activities
in the Game, including your achievements, rating, etc.
The data we receive
from third-party resources
We do not purposefully
collect data from third-party resources, but we can do this to facilitate your
user experience (for example, to identify you in the game, as well as when you
interact with ads).
• “
Your data related
to a third–party resource
” - information about your login (for example,
email address) on a third-party resource through which you log in to the Game
(for example, via Facebook).
• “
Advertising ID
”
is a unique identifier that is associated with your mobile phone or tablet,
used by advertisers to track ads.
