Does Axlebolt collect
my financial information when I make in-app purchases?
When you make in-app
purchases in the Game, we do not collect data about the payment transactions
you make and do not have access to your payment information. This information
is collected and stored by your platform (for example, the App Store on Apple
devices, Google Play on Android devices, or the App Gallery on Huawei devices)
or by your platform's payment operator.
We have the opportunity
to receive data about payments made by you through third-party services (if you
contact us with a request from a payment operator, bank, or other third-party
payment provider) for the purpose of verifying payments from you. However, we
do not intentionally collect or store this data.
Please note that
purchases of in-app objects can be carried out not only through the
functionality of the Game, but also through the stores of third-party services
authorized by us. We encourage you to review the privacy policies of such
third-party services.
In specific cases your
data might be collected in order to process your refund requests, which also
require your consent as provided in this Privacy Policy (see Section “How my
data is used for refunds?”).
Data usage
How is my personal
data used for analytics?
As a Game developer, it
is important to us to know how users interact with our Games in order to
improve your user experience. We and our partners (“Analytics Services”)
collect your Location Information, Device Information, Advertising IDs, and Login
information for analytics purposes for our Games. For example, we use this
information to:
• assessment of the
difficulty level of the Game,
• corrections of any
errors in the Game,
• assessing the
demographics of our users,
• determining the need
to support a new type of Device for the Game.
In some cases, the
Analytics Services collect information about you on our behalf and act as a Processor
of your personal data, and in some cases, the Analytics Services independently
decide to collect your personal data through mechanisms built into our
applications. In the latter case, Analytics Services acts as a Controller under
the EU General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR).
We recommend that you
familiarize yourself with the list of our Analytics Services and their privacy
policies:
