Where does Axlebolt store my data?
We store data in
Germany (Frankfurt), which provides an adequate level of data protection.
The data is stored by
AMAZON WEB SERVICES EMEA SARL (CC OTH 00760863 2022 TR). You can read
the privacy policy
of AMAZON WEB SERVICES.
By agreeing to the
Policy, you consent to the transfer of Personal Data to the territory of
Germany.
How long will Axlebolt store my personal data?
We store your personal
data while you are playing the Game. We reserve the right to store your
personal data for 1 year (or any other period established by applicable law)
after you stop playing the Game.
We will store your
personal data for 1 year after you stop playing the Game in order to save your
progress in the game and purchases in case you decide to resume activity in our
Game, as well as in case government authorities contact us with requests for
information about your transactions in the Game.
The right to delete
If you want to
completely delete your account and personal data, which we are obliged to
delete immediately upon your request, you can contact us at
privacy@axlebolt.com
.
After deleting your
information or after 1 year has elapsed since your last gaming session, your
account will be deleted and your game progress and purchases will be lost.
Does Axlebolt process children's personal data?
Our Game is rated as
having content suitable for those aged 16 years and older. We do not knowingly
collect children's personal data.
If you are the parent
of a child under the age of 16 who plays our Game, you can request the deletion
of your child's personal data and prohibit us from further collecting his
personal data by writing to us at
privacy@axlebolt.com
.
If your child contacts
the support service, we will delete his email address and other personal data
immediately after responding to his request, if we become aware that your child
is under 16 years old.
Do third-party services process my personal
data?
In our Game, you may
see links to third-party websites or applications (for example, in
advertisements). Please note that when you click on links to third-party
websites or applications, you can share your personal data with such websites
or applications. Axlebolt does not control the collection of personal data by
third-party websites or applications, and we recommend that you read their
privacy policies in advance.
Social media functions and tools
The Game may include
integrated social media features and tools such as the «Like» button on
Facebook, the «Share» button on YouTube, and the «Subscribe» button on Twitter.
These tools may collect information about your IP address. Social media
features and tools are hosted on third-party servers, and your interaction with
these social media features and tools is governed by the privacy policies of
such social networks.
How does Axlebolt ensure the security of my
personal data?
The security of your
personal information is important to us. We follow generally accepted industry
standards to protect your information, both during transmission and once it is
received. However, no method of transmission over the Internet, or method of
electronic storage, is 100% secure. Therefore, we cannot guarantee its absolute
security. While no security system is completely secure, we and our partners
stake appropriate security measures to protect against unauthorized access or
disclosure of the information collected by us. For Axlebolt, this includes, but
is not limited to, ensuring that all of your information is disclosed only on a
“need to know” basis and ensuring that all information collected by Axlebolt is
done so via secured connections and protected and encrypted by industrial grade
security software to guard against unauthorized access.
Sharing your personal information for
business/legal reasons
A.
Business Transfers. As we continue to develop our
business, we may reorganize as a business entity, acquire entities,
subsidiaries, or business units, or enter into joint ventures with
third-parties. In any of these types of transactions, any information you
provide may be one of the transferred business assets (subject to any
pre-existing privacy notice unless you consent otherwise). In the event that
all or substantially all of our assets are acquired or we merge with a
third-party, your information will likely be one of the transferred assets. You
understand and agree that we reserve the right to transfer any information
collected from you in the case of any such transfer. In such event, we will use
reasonable efforts to notify you before information about you is transferred
and becomes subject to a different privacy policy.
B.
Legal. We may disclose information you provide to
respond to subpoenas, court orders, requests from authorities, and other legal
process, and to establish/exercise our legal rights. We may also disclose your
information to defend against legal claims when we believe that disclosure is
necessary to protect our rights, protect your safety or the safety of others,
investigate fraud, or respond to a government request. We may share your
information in order to investigate, prevent or take action regarding illegal
activities, suspected fraud, and situations involving potential threats to the
physical safety of any person, violations of our License Agreement, or as
otherwise required by law.
Please note that we may
transfer your account information if you request a refund through Apple
services. By submitting such a request to Apple, you agree to the transfer of
your data. We recommend that you read the
Apple Privacy Policy
.
Is my personal data sold to any third parties?
No, Axlebolt does not
sell personal data of the users of the Game to any third parties and has never
tried to sell any personal data.
How do I access, manage, or update my personal
information?
Please contact us at
privacy@axlebolt.com
.
What rights do I have?
For users in the European Union
If you are a resident
of the European Union, you have rights under applicable data protection laws.
These include:
• The right of access.
You have the right to request and receive a copy of your data available to us;
• The right to
correction or deletion. You have the right to request the correction or
deletion of your data available to us;
• The right to restrict
processing. You have the right to restrict the processing of your data at our
disposal;
• The right to data
portability. You have the right to transfer your data at our disposal (transfer
the data to another controller). At the same time, we are not responsible for
the compatibility of data with a third-party service.
In certain
circumstances, you may also have the right to object to the processing of your
data. To send such a request, please use the contact information provided in
the "
Contact us
"
section. We will review any such request and take action in accordance with
applicable data protection laws.
If we rely on your
consent to the processing of your personal data, you have the right to withdraw
your consent at any time. However, this will not affect the legality of
processing until such consent is revoked. Please also note that in addition to
your consent, we may have other legitimate grounds for processing certain
categories of data, so if you disagree with their processing, you must delete
your account in the Game.
Transfer of personal
data outside the EU. Since some of our Analytics Services, Advertising
Partners, and Third-party resources for fighting are located in countries
outside the European Union, your personal data may be transferred to countries
that may not provide the same level of data privacy as the laws of your country
of residence. When transferring data across borders, we rely solely on the
legitimate grounds for such transfer.
Although we and our
partners take all reasonable and necessary measures to protect your personal
data from unauthorized access by third parties, we are obliged to inform you
about the possible risks of such storage of your personal data in jurisdictions
outside the European Union in accordance with Article 49(1)(a) GDPR.
By agreeing to the
processing of your personal data in accordance with this Privacy Policy and by
playing the Game, you give us your
express consent to the cross-border
transfer of your personal data.
For residents of the Russian Federation
If you are a personal
data subject from the Russian Federation, then you have the right to ensure the
protection of your rights and freedoms when processing personal Data,
protection of the rights to privacy, personal and family secrets, in particular
you have the right:
• require us, as an
operator, to clarify your Personal data, block or destroy it if the personal data
is incomplete, outdated, inaccurate, illegally obtained or is not necessary for
the stated purpose of processing, as well as take legal measures to protect
your rights;
• to receive
information related to the processing of your Personal Data, including:
confirmation of the fact of processing Personal Data by the operator; legal
grounds and purposes of processing Personal Data; purposes and methods of
processing Personal Data used by the operator; name and location of the
operator, information about persons (except for employees of the operator) who
have access to Personal Data or to whom Personal Data may be disclosed on the
basis of an agreement with the operator or on the basis of Federal Law;
processed Personal Data related to the relevant Personal Data subject, the
source of their receipt; terms of processing of Personal Data, including the
terms of their storage; information about the performed or proposed cross-border
data transfer; name or surname, first name, patronymic and address of the
person processing Personal Data on behalf of the operator, if processing is
entrusted or will be assigned to such a person; other information;
• to protect their
rights and legitimate interests, including compensation for damages and (or)
compensation for moral damage in court.
For residents of Brazil
If Brazilian law
applies to the processing of your Personal Data, you have the right to request
from Axlebolt:
• confirmation of the
fact of data processing;
• access to processed
data;
• correction of
incomplete, inaccurate or outdated data;
• Anonymization,
blocking or deletion of unnecessary, redundant data or data processed in
violation of the provisions of the Brazilian Data Protection Act (LGPD);
• the possibility of
transferring data to another service or product provider through a direct
request in accordance with the requirements of the National Data protection
Authority (ANPD) and taking into account the requirements of commercial and
industrial secrets;
• deletion of personal
data processed with your consent;
• information about
public and private organizations with which Axlebolt has shared data;
• information about the
possibility of refusal of consent and the consequences of such refusal.
You can also withdraw
your consent to the processing of Personal Data, object to the processing
carried out on the basis of one of the situations of refusal of consent, if
there is a violation of the provisions of the LGPD. We do not make decisions
based solely on automated processing of Personal Data, however, in any case you
have the right to review decisions made solely on the basis of automated
processing of personal data affecting your interests, including decisions aimed
at determining your personal, professional, consumer and credit profile or
other aspects of your personality.
For data subjects located in the Republic of
Turkey
The Personal Data
Protection Act No. 6698 (“DPL”) contains the rights of data subjects accessing
services from the Republic of Turkey. You have the right to contact the data
controller in order to:
• find out if your
personal data is being processed;
• request information
about whether your personal data has been processed;
• find out the purpose
of processing your personal data and whether this personal data is used in
accordance with the purpose;
• know the third
parties to whom your personal data is transferred in the country or abroad;
• request correction of
incomplete or inaccurate data, if any;
• request the deletion
of your personal data in accordance with the conditions specified in Article 7
of the DPL;
• request reporting on
transactions carried out in certain cases from third parties to whom your
personal data has been transferred;
• independently object
to the occurrence of a result in relation to this person by analyzing data
processed exclusively using automated systems;
• claim compensation
for damages resulting from the illegal processing of your personal data.
For residents of California
The California Consumer
Privacy Protection Act ("CCPA") grants California residents the
following rights:
The right to
access/inform. You have the right to request that we provide you with the
following information:
•
categories
and specific elements of Personal Data that we have collected about you over
the past 12 months;
•
categories
of sources from which we collect Personal Data;
•
business
or commercial purposes for the collection, use, exchange or sale of Personal
Data;
•
the
categories of Personal Data that we have disclosed about you for commercial
purposes and the categories of recipients to whom they have been disclosed;
•
categories
of Personal Data that we have sold or transferred, and categories of third parties
to whom each type of Personal Data has been sold or transferred.
•
The
right to delete. You have the right to request that we delete Personal Data
under certain circumstances, with some exceptions.
•
The
right to correction. You have the right to request that we correct the Personal
Data that we store about you if you believe that it is inaccurate. We may
request the relevant documents from you in connection with your request. After
receiving and validating a request to correct inaccurate Personal Data, we will
make all commercially reasonable efforts to correct the Personal Data.
•
The
right of refusal. We do not sell your Personal Data. However, in any case, you
have the right to refuse the sale and exchange of your Personal Data.
•
If you
wish to opt out of the sale and sharing, except through Cookies or other online
tracking technologies, you can contact us using the methods listed below in the
"Contact Us" section.
•
The
right to non-discrimination. You have the right not to be discriminated against
for exercising the rights set out in the CCPA.
Contact the data protection authorities
For residents of the European
Union
: If you live in the European
Union and believe that we are illegally processing your personal data, you have
the right to file a complaint with the local data protection supervisory
authority. You can find contact information here:
https://commission.europa.eu/about-european-commission/contact_en
.
For residents of the
Russian Federation
: if
you believe that your rights are being violated, you can contact the Authorized
Body for the Protection of the rights of personal data subjects – Federal
Service for Supervision of Communications. You can find contact information at:
https://rkn.gov.ru/contacts /
.
For residents of Brazil
: if you believe that our interaction with your personal
data violates applicable law, you can send a corresponding request to the
Brazilian Data Protection Authority (ANPD).
For California
residents
: If you are a CCPA
subject, you have the right to file a complaint with the California Data
Protection Agency at the following email address:
PRA@cppa.ca.gov
.
For residents of the
Republic of Turkey
: if
you believe that your rights are being violated, you can contact the Office for
Personal Data Protection. You can find contact information here:
https://www.kvkk.gov.tr/Icerik/6655/Contact-Us
.
Contact us
If you want to exercise
the above rights or contact us for another reason, please contact us at
privacy@axlebolt.com
.
You can also write to
us at: Christodoulou Chatzipavlou, 221, Helios Court, Flat 401, 3036, Limassol,
Cyprus.
Please note that in
order to fulfill the request, we may need additional information to identify
the person who contacted us. If the provision of information may lead to a
violation of the rights and legitimate interests of third parties, we may
refuse to provide information.
To exercise the rights
mentioned above, your request must contain the following information:
• your email address;
• information
confirming that you are connected to us, or information otherwise confirming
that we process your personal data.
Thank you for choosing
our Game!
With respect,
The Axlebolt command
